EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to county fire protection districts; requiring the
Washoe County Board of County Commissioners, Reno
City Council and Sparks City Council to establish a board
to conduct a study relating to the creation of a county fire
protection district within certain territory; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes contiguous unincorporated territory lying within one or
2 more counties or incorporated territory lying within a consolidated municipality
3 and not included in any other fire protection district to, by petition and election, be
4 formed into a county fire protection district. (NRS 474.010-474.125) Existing law
5 also authorizes a board of county commissioners to, by ordinance, organize
6 unincorporated territory within the county into a county fire protection district.
7 (NRS 474.460) Existing law further authorizes a board of county commissioners in
8 a county whose population is less than 700,000 (currently all counties other than
9 Clark County) to consolidate two or more county fire protection districts within the
10 county under certain circumstances. (NRS 474.533)
11 Section 15 of this bill requires: (1) the Washoe County Board of County
12 Commissioners, the Reno City Council and the Sparks City Council to establish, by
13 interlocal agreement, a board to study the creation of a county fire protection
14 district to consolidate fire protection services within certain territory within Washoe
15 County, Reno and Sparks; and (2) the board to prepare a written report of the
16 results and any recommendations.
