15 Sec. 15. 1. The Washoe County Board of County
16 Commissioners shall, by interlocal agreement adopted in accordance
17 with the provisions of NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, establish
18 a board to study the creation of a county fire protection district to
19 consolidate fire protection services within territory within Washoe
20 County and the Cities of Reno and Sparks. Washoe County and the
21 Cities of Reno and Sparks shall share the costs of the study, the
22 costs of any additional consultants and experts and any other cost
23 necessary to conduct the study.
24 2. The board established pursuant to subsection 1 must be
25 composed of:
26 (a) Two members of the Washoe County Board of County
27 Commissioners, appointed by the Washoe County Board of County
28 Commissioners;
29 (b) Two members of the Reno City Council, appointed by the
30 Reno City Council; and
31 (c) Two members of the Sparks City Council, appointed by the
32 Sparks City Council.
33 3. The board shall:
34 (a) Evaluate the impact a consolidated county fire protection
35 district will have on the response times, preparation and costs of
36 providing fire protection services in Washoe County and the Cities
37 of Reno and Sparks;
38 (b) Determine any legal mechanisms necessary to consolidate
39 fire service between the County and the Cities;
40 (c) Determine any assessments necessary to support the district;
41 (d) Determine and review the amount of any debt and liabilities
42 of each former fire protection district or fire department
