13 4. A majority of members constitutes a quorum at any meeting.
14 Any action of the board must be approved by a majority of members
15 and at least one member appointed by each participating governing
16 body.
17 5. The board may contract with other entities to assist the board
18 in carrying out the requirements of this section.
19 6. The board established pursuant to subsection 1 is a public
20 body and is subject to the requirements set forth in chapter 241 of
21 NRS.
